rComments: The course offers at uottawa only and topic is really interesting. load of work is high but easy to get good mark, the software was not so user friendly. The online access to software was really good since you can do your work anywhere you like.

It was really worth to have CWM for this semester. I really strive to get more from this subject. The teaching sessions were exceptional and the term-project and lab works gave actual welding engineering experience.
The course is not easy with many mathematical work. The prof is very supportive and gives lots of incentive for good mark.
The prof was always available to answer questions by email or office. I felt comfortable to ask many questions

The course content is complex , and the load of work including 6 serious assignments and a software-based term project keeps you busy for the whole semester. However the marking scheme is well distributed and not concentrated on exams. At the end the average of class got a good mark.
